<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CONCORDIA DOWNS THE MASTER'S IN GAME SHORTENED BY RAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Concordia scored three runs in the second inning and four in the fourth to 
beat The Master's, 7-4, in a rain-shortened, five-inning game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles also scored three runs in the sixth, but that inning was washed 
out. 
</P>
<P>
 Doug Senne had two hits, with a double and two runs batted in to lead 
Concordia (16-25-1). Jason Freeman, in his first start for The Master's, hit a 
home run. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's tennis: 
</P>
