<TEXT>
<P>
 Dereck Ornelas hit a pair of home runs, including a grand slam, to lead 
Mission College to a 20-11 victory over Cerro Coso on Wednesday at Ridgecrest, 
clinching its first Southern California Athletic Conference baseball 
championship. Raymond Rivera pitched a complete game for Mission (25-15, 17-7 
in conference play) and set a school record with his 12th victory of the 
season. HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL 
</P>
