<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLUB REVIEW; 'LEGENDS' HEATS UP IN OJAI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEIDI SIEGMUND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mineral springs, jazz and thou: the perfect date. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Wheeler Hot Springs in Ojai has been bubbling for 103 years, the 
"Legends of Jazz" series being offered in the venue's supper club has heated 
the place up considerably.Live jazz is featured Thursday through Sunday. 
Weeknight reservations are easier to come by, but the "Legends" series on 
Sunday evenings is worth calling ahead for. With a remarkable lineup of jazz 
greats, the semi-monthly program is the ultimate setting for a dream date 
because, like, Calgon, it takes you away.  
</P>
<P>
 A raised stage at one end of the quaint, rustic restaurant is the evening's 
focal point. April's guests included trumpeter Harry (Sweets) Edison and 
guitarist Herb Ellis playing with pianist Roger Kellaway. 
</P>
<P>
 A series of French doors behind the stage enable you to look out toward the 
mountain landscape, and because many of the artists are famous from an earlier 
era, the whole evening feels far more special than the usual supper club fare. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's wonderful to be up at this place," noted Edison during a recent 
performance. "With me, at my age, it's wonderful to be anyplace." 
</P>
<P>
 * Wheeler Hot Springs, 16826 Maricopa Highway (Highway 33), advance 
reservations required . (800) 227-9292. Dinner and jazz on Sundays, $50 per 
person. HEIDI SIEGMUND 
</P>
</TEXT>
