<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS / HOLLYWOOD: QUAKE AID RELOCATES TO SERVICE CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The last disaster application center that opened after the Northridge quake 
closed last weekend and the operation was transferred to an earthquake service 
center in Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The service center opened Monday at 6385 Hollywood Blvd. It will be open 9 
a.m. to 6 p.m. daily except Sundays. 
</P>
<P>
 At the peak of the emergency following the Jan. 17 quake, state and federal 
disaster relief officials operated 21 disaster application centers. 
</P>
<P>
 To date 126,923 people have registered for aid at the centers, while another 
402,121 filed applications through the telephone registration line. 
</P>
