 EXPLORING HOME: There's a new boat pulling into Dana Point Harbor on Saturday 
after a three-week trip from Florida.And it plans to stay. The Sea Explorer 
will be the county's first ship dedicated to educating the public about marine 
environment. . . . The Orange County Marine Institute bought it to replace 
various boats it has had to lease for such education projects. The 70-foot 
vessel arrives at 11:30 a.m. You can go aboard the boat for a look between noon 
and 2. 
