<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; TAKE YOUR 
DAUGHTER TO WORK ON METROLINK -- FREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you are planning to take your daughter to work today for "Take Our 
Daughters to Work Day," the Metrolink rail system will get them there for free. 
</P>
<P>
 Metrolink will allow one child 18 years or younger to ride the train free when 
accompanied by a fare-paying adult.  
</P>
<P>
 "Kids need to understand that driving to work alone is not an example we 
should perpetuate," said Metrolink Chairman Larry Walker.  
</P>
<P>
 "By taking the train to work and working alongside adult role models, children 
will have a rare opportunity to gain insights into their ability to contribute 
to the economy and society," Walker said. 
