<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 AFTERSHOCKS RATTLE THE VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two more aftershocks of the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake were felt on the 
western side of the aftershock zone early Wednesday, Caltech reported.The 
strongest, magnitude 3.5, occurred at 5:33 a.m. and was centered one mile 
southwest of Simi Valley. There was also a magnitude 3.1 jolt at 2:39 a.m., 
centered three miles northwest of Chatsworth. 
</P>
<P>
 Altogether, there have been more than 6,000 aftershocks of the Northridge 
earthquake, a Caltech spokeswoman said. 
</P>
