<P>
DANCING TO DIVERSITY IN COVINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ishita Patel, 16, blends traditional Rajesthani and Gujrati dance styles this 
month at Charter Oak High School's Unity Festival.The Covina school's festival 
celebrated 13 of the school's many cultures, including Indian, Korean, Chinese, 
Japanese, African, Native American and European. Traditional costumes and foods 
formed a backdrop to performances that included belly dancing and flamenco. The 
school's Unity Club formed this year to mitigate racial tensions that flared 
last fall. "We're trying to use the cultural diversity at our school as a 
resource, rather than a source of conflict," said club Vice President Sapna 
Patel. 
</P>
