</P>
<P>
 Kevin Schramm of the Citrus baseball team had his 35-game hitting streak end 
during a 2-1 Foothill Conference victory over College of the Desert. 
</P>
<P>
 Schramm, whose streak dated to last season, had entered the game with a .549 
average and 12 home runs and 49 runs batted in. Citrus, under Coach Skip 
Claprood, began this week 27-4 and 17-1 in the conference. 
</P>
