 Pomona-Pitzer's baseball team enters this weekend's Southern California 
Intercollegiate Athletic Conference series against Caltech having set several 
school records. 
</P>
<P>
 Pomona-Pitzer, coming off its first sweep of Claremont-Mudd, began the week 
18-12 and in third-place in the SCIAC at 11-7. Pomona-Pitzer has already 
eclipsed its record of 10 SCIAC wins set last season. The Sagehens will finish 
above .500 in conference for the first time since 1957 and will finish above 
.500 overall for the first time since 1969. The 18 victories are the most since 
1957, when the Sagehens finished 23-11. 
</P>
<P>
 Jarrod Kula is batting .606 and Emiliano Escandon is hitting .453 in 
conference games for the Sagehens, who will participate in the SCIAC tournament 
May 5-7. 
