<HEADLINE>
<P>
AGOURA HILLS GIRL, 8, FINDS MOTHER SLAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS and CHAU LAM, TIMES STAFF WRITERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 36-year-old woman who had been stabbed several times was discovered dead 
inside her condominium Wednesday morning by her young daughter. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Robin McLean, who lived in the Steeplechase Condominiums on North Lost Hills 
Road, was stabbed several times in the chest, according to Los Angeles County 
sheriff's investigators.The 8-year-old girl, whose name is being withheld by 
police, discovered her mother's body about 7:30 a.m. when she woke up. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl did not hear her mother being attacked, Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Lt. Joe Brown said, and there were no signs of a forced entry into the 
two-bedroom unit. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's unusual (that) it happened rather quietly," Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators believe that someone stabbed McLean several times in the chest 
with a knife during the night late Tuesday or early Wednesday, Brown said. But 
detectives have not located the murder weapon and know no motive for the 
attack. 
</P>
<P>
 They declined to say in which room the body was found. 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, neighbors in the large, gated complex described McLean as 
committed to her daughter, but said they did not know much about her. 
</P>
<P>
 "She was very involved with her child," said Jeff Ames, the president of the 
homeowners association. "She was very nice and sociable." 
</P>
</TEXT>
