<P>
ARMIJO RETURNS TO RING TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a year layoff, Huntington Beach's John (The Fighting Lifeguard) Armijo 
is returning to the ring in tonight's 10-round main event at the Irvine 
Marriott Ballroom. 
</P>
<P>
 Armijo's last fight, in May, 1993, was a loss to super-welterweight Kenny 
Lopez in a 12-round decision.Since then, Armijo (14-7 with six knockouts) has 
dropped 11 pounds, and he will fight Chuck Goossen of North Hollywood at 143 
pounds, three pounds over the lightweight limit. Goossen, a cousin of promoter 
Dan Goossen, is 6-1 with five knockouts and is 10 years younger than Armijo, 
32. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-fight undercard features middleweight Rodney Toney (11-0 with five 
knockouts) of Campo against Irvine's Luis Mejia (6-5) in a six-round bout. 
</P>
<P>
 In another undercard fight, Los Angeles junior lightweight Leonard Fiqueirof 
is taking on San Diego's Bryan Cimicata, who is making his pro debut. Tickets 
for the 7:30 p.m. show are priced at $25, $30 and $35 and can be purchased at 
the ballroom. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
