</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Washington defensive lineman D'Marco Farr, Miami defensive lineman Kevin 
Patrick and Purdue wide receiver Jermaine Ross are among 10 rookie free agents 
expected to sign with the Rams today, said Jay Zygmunt, Rams' senior vice 
president. 
</P>
<P>
 Also expected to sign are Notre Dame quarterback Kevin McDougal and New Mexico 
wide receiver Turhon O'Bannon, who came to terms with the team Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Bannon, the half-brother of UCLA basketball stars Ed and Charles O'Bannon, 
had 47 catches last season and scored seven touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 McDougal has said he will play in the Canadian Football League if he cannot 
catch on in the NFL. The Winnipeg Blue Bombers own the rights to McDougal and 
Florida State quarterback Charlie Ward, who is considering pro basketball. 
</P>
<P>
 "Maybe Charlie and I didn't do enough to prove ourselves," McDougal told the 
Associated Press Wednesday. "All we did was take our teams to No. 1 and No. 2 
in the country." 
</P>
<P>
 Linebacker Joe Kelly, whom the Raiders cut last week, worked out Wednesday for 
the Rams. 
</P>
<P>
