<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRL GETS $3,730 IN KIDDIE BANK HEIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 11-year-old girl stole $3,730 from a bank by simply grabbing bagfuls of 
money from the counter, court officials in Dundee, Scotland, said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 But she was not about to share the loot with her 12-year-old male accomplice 
-- she gave him just one pound ($1.50) to buy candy. 
</P>
<P>
 The officials said the girl admitted stealing the money last July. 
</P>
<P>
 Police found a rucksack containing about a third of the stolen money in the 
girl's house, the court was told Tuesday. The girl told police she had spent 
some of her haul and buried the rest. It was never recovered. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy, who pleaded guilty to a charge of receiving $3,730, was given one bag 
of money by the girl outside the bank. But on the way home, she retrieved it 
and gave him a one-pound coin to buy candy, the court heard. The two will be 
sentenced in three weeks. 
</P>
