<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: AIRLINES CLEANED UP ON THIS MISCUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The final bill has been tallied for the Hoover vacuum cleaner company's 
disastrous free-flights promotion -- and it's a whopper.Hoover, overwhelmed by 
the response to an offer of free international tickets to English and Irish 
purchasers of appliances, spent $72 million. 
</P>
<P>
 When the promotion ends, Hoover will have flown more than 220,000 people for 
free. Consumers realized the obvious: that vacuum cleaners are cheaper than 
international air fares. So they bought Hoovers by the thousands and demanded 
tickets. 
</P>
