<TEXT>
<P>
 Next week is Small Business Week, a time to honor the role that small 
companies play in both employment and services. 
</P>
<P>
 But the federal Small Business Administration and the Orange County Chamber of 
Commerce & Industry will get a head start today with a luncheon honoring a 
number of successful local business people. 
</P>
<P>
 Honorees include Mark Press, president of Gold Coast Baking Co. in Santa Ana; 
Judee Slack of Slack & Associates accounting firm in Fountain Valley; the Elena 
Nunez and Associates accounting firm in Fullerton; and John Hall, president of 
guitar maker Rickenbacker International Corp. in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 The luncheon will take place from 11:30 a.m. to 1:45 p.m. at the Westin South 
Coast Plaza Hotel in Costa Mesa. Tickets are $39.50 at the door. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Ana Economic Development Corp. will mark the small business 
community's contributions May 5 with a breakfast to award members of the city's 
business community. 
</P>
<P>
 The agency will name accounting firm owner Jo Ann Rayfield the city's 
entrepreneur of the year; Bank of America, which over the past two years has 
provided Orange County businesses nearly $3 million in financing through its 
participation in an SBA loan program, will be honored as lender of the year; 
IBM Corp., a business partner with Saddleback High School since 1988, has been 
selected for the "business and education linkage contributor" award. 
</P>
<P>
 The breakfast will be at the Turnip Rose restaurant, 3 Imperial Promenade, in 
Santa Ana. The cost is $20 in advance and $25 at the door. For more 
information, call the Santa Ana Economic Development Corp. at (714) 647-6987. 
