</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marion Merrell Dow Inc. said its first-quarter profit rose 16%, led by 
increased sales of its Cardizem heart drugs. 
</P>
<P>
 The Kansas City, Mo., company earned $85 million, or 31 cents per share, in 
the three months ended March 31, compared to $73 million, or 26 cents per 
share, in the same period a year earlier. Sales rose 15% to $708 million from 
$617 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Sales of Cardizem drugs rose 16% to $241 million; sales of Seldane allergy 
medications increased 7% to $154 million; sales of the Carafate ulcer drug fell 
6% to $33 million, and sales of Nicoderm patches fell 50% to $18 million. 
</P>
