<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: LONG BEACH WOMAN GAINS SEAT ON DEVELOPMENT BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Victoria Rodriguez Fullerton of Long Beach has been named to the board of 
directors of the California American Woman's Economic Development Corp., a 
nonprofit organization that provides business training for women interested in 
starting or expanding businesses. Fullerton helped found Long Beach-based MRA 
Inc., which offers services to contain health care costs. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Goodwill Industries of Long Beach and South Bay recently appointed Linda Lee 
Saleski as president and chief executive officer. Saleski held a similar 
position with Goodwill in Macon, Ga. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Cerritos High School senior Melissa Wiley and Millikan High School senior 
Louis Wharton have won $2,000 National Achievement Scholarships. They were 
among 600 young black Americans who competed for the privately funded 
scholarship, which were begun in 1964 to honor black students and increase 
their educational opportunities. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Executives Assn. of Long Beach, a group with businesses in the greater 
Long Beach area, has announced its 1994-95 officers: President Al Oberjuerge of 
Oberjuerge Auto Repair, Vice President Roger Lockwood of Earthscapes Custom 
Landscaping and Secretary Doug Shea of INCO Co. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Long Beach-based cable television comedy team of Ron Petke and Ed Bell 
have been nominated to receive a 1994 local CableAce Award given by the 
National Academy of Cable Programming to recognize outstanding achievement in 
local cable television. The comedy team has appeared intermittently since the 
late '70s on CVI Cablevision Industries channel in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach City College students Andrew Ashton and Daniel Reeder, both of Long 
Beach, and Anna Mota of Lakewood have won the General Motors Spirit Award, 
given to outstanding Long Beach City College students. 
</P>
