HOT TICKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stung by his penchant for perfection, New Yorkers derided Pierre Boulez as 
"The French Correction." But Angelenos have enjoyed his deceptively stern 
company since 1969. The composer conducts the Philharmonic at the Music Center 
tonight through Saturday at 8 and Sunday at 2:30. 
</P>
