<P>
L.A. PRODUCTION TO OUTSHINE O.C.'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Diane Haithman 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The production of "The Who's Tommy" at the Universal Amphitheatre in July will 
be more lavish than the production next month at the Orange County Performing 
Arts Center in Costa Mesa, according to Scott Zeiger, executive producer of the 
"Tommy" tour. 
</P>
<P>
 "L.A. will be unique unto itself," Zeiger said. Costa Mesa and other cities 
along the route "will have a wonderful production, but L.A. is going to have a 
custom design that is going to be quite spectacular. Universal Amphitheatre is 
such a unique space; it's not a traditional proscenium stage. We are spending a 
great deal of time building a special set design."Diane Haithman 
