</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 32-year-old Ventura man was critically wounded by a gunman who walked up and 
shot him while he was waiting at a stop sign in his minivan, police said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnny Edward Rios was in critical condition at Ventura County Medical Center 
on Wednesday, a nursing supervisor said.He suffered at least one gunshot wound 
to the head, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rios was driving the minivan belonging to his family's janitorial service 
north on Callens Road about 11 p.m. Tuesday when he braked for a stop sign at 
Market Street, Ventura Police Sgt. Bob Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 While Rios was stopped, a man wearing dark clothing and a ski mask walked 
across the street in front of the van and suddenly pulled out a handgun and 
began firing at Rios and a co-worker, Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We haven't discovered a reason why, at this point," Anderson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The gunman fled as the wounded Rios drove across the intersection. He crashed 
the van into a bus bench and mailbox, Anderson said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
