<HEADLINE>
<P>
'FOXES, HARES, BEARS' THEME OF YOUTH FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free educational youth fair that attracted more than 12,000 people last year 
is scheduled for Friday through Sunday at the county fairgrounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Youth Expo will have hundreds of student competitions in subjects ranging from 
poetry to cattle raising.There will be a jazz festival, science and engineering 
project demonstrations, a talent search, a carnival and other attractions. 
</P>
<P>
 Almost 9,000 young people entered competitions last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The theme of this year's expo is "foxes, hares and golden bears," and there 
will be displays of California mammals. A group of young people who volunteer 
to help the Orange County Animal Control will display live rabbits and a 
mounted fox and bear. 
</P>
<P>
 The expo will run from 9 a.m. to 7 p.m. on Friday and Saturday, and from 9 
a.m. to 5 p.m. on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
